      "question": "If $\\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle PQR$ and $\\frac{AB}{PQ} = \\frac{1}{3}$, then the ratio of their areas $\\frac{\\text{Area}(\\triangle ABC)}{\\text{Area}(\\triangle PQR)}$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recall the theorem: The ratio of areas of two similar triangles is equal to the square of the ratio of their corresponding sides.",
          "Calculate the square of the given ratio: $(\\frac{1}{3})^2$.",
          "Result is $\\frac{1}{9}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{\\text{Area}(ABC)}{\\text{Area}(PQR)} = \\left(\\frac{AB}{PQ}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1}{9}"
      },
